name: Andrew McCarthy
summary: Andrew McCarthy's recent documentary, "Brats," explores the lasting impact of the "Brat Pack" label on his career. In interviews, McCarthy reveals that he and Jon Cryer had a strained relationship during that era. McCarthy also revisits the criticisms and controversies surrounding the "Brat Pack" phenomenon, including the absence of Molly Ringwald and Judd Nelson in his documentary. He discusses the stigmatizing effects of the label and the challenges of living up to expectations. McCarthy expresses doubt that the "Brat Pack" could exist in today's cultural landscape and reflects on the treatment of Virginia Madsen on the set of "Class." Additionally, he acknowledges the role of "Brat Pack" co-stars Rob Lowe and the importance of their support in his efforts to reclaim his narrative.

name: Johnny Canales
summary: Tejano music icon and TV host Johnny Canales has passed away at age 77, leaving an enduring legacy in the industry. Canales was a pioneer in promoting Tejano music, hosting a popular television show that showcased emerging artists, including the legendary Selena. His contributions to Tejano culture, including his tireless advocacy for its recognition and his dedication to preserving its traditions, have earned him widespread acclaim. The news of his passing has sent shockwaves throughout the Tejano community and beyond, with many mourning the loss of a beloved figure who dedicated his life to celebrating and promoting their musical heritage.

In other news, the Supreme Court has dismissed a trademark case involving former President Donald Trump's slogan "Trump too small." The Court faces a substantial backlog of cases with limited time to address them.
